examples.en: Russell was deeply moved by what he heard.
He moved closer to her.
I was truly moved by his tears.
examples.ru: Я был по-настоящему растроган его слезами.

examples.en: Her fate moved us all.
We moved into the shade.
The pound moved up a little today.
In the shadows something moved.
They've moved up north.
She moved to a bigger city.
examples.ru: Она переехала в более крупный город.

examples.en: They moved the furniture about.
He was moved by her obvious concern.
examples.ru: Он был тронут её несомненной заботой.

examples.en: He moved out of danger
He moved at a rattling pace.
She moved to a smaller town.
She moved with sinuous grace.
The traffic moved at a creep.
examples.ru: Череда машин в пробке еле-еле ползла.

examples.en: A dark shape moved behind them.
They moved the meeting date up.
examples.ru: Они перенесли дату совещания на более ранний срок.

examples.en: Interest rates have moved down.
The family next door moved away.
We moved from Idaho to Nebraska.
examples.ru: Мы переехали из Айдахо в Небраску.

examples.en: He moved his family to Virginia.
examples.ru: Он переехал с семьей в Вирджинию.

examples.en: He moved towards her menacingly.
Share prices moved up this month.
examples.ru: В этом месяце цены на акции выросли.

examples.en: They moved to somewhere in Spain.
I moved out into the second lane.
'Come on,' Sue said. No one moved.
examples.ru: — Пойдёмте же, — сказала Сью. Никто не пошевелился.

examples.en: She moved with an unstudied grace.
She moved lightly across the room.
Father Doyle moved to a new parish.
examples.ru: Отец Дойл переехал в новый приход.
